# .git-sha and .flux-app-version are intentionally NOT ignored.
# `npm run deploy` writes both (git rev-parse HEAD > .git-sha and
# git rev-parse HEAD:flux-klein-server > .flux-app-version), and the
# orchestrator reads .flux-app-version at startup for the volume drift
# check (.git-sha is forensic context only, since RAILWAY_GIT_COMMIT_SHA
# is empty under `railway up` CLI deploys). Railway CLI honors .gitignore
# during upload, so adding either file here causes it to be skipped and
# the drift check silently no-ops in production. Both files will appear
# as untracked after each deploy — that's expected.
